performance::check_model(exp1allglm, check = c("qq"))

probably analyse 1:2 hard and soft for feeding behaviour

need to make day a separate variable for separate experiments!! maybe? but it looks like it understands it with emmeans so might be fine egg counting data works fine to be combined but are the experiments too different?

using: emmeans::emmeans(exp1bothlm, specs = pairwise ~ diet) not using day and experiment in the model

1:2H - 1:2S -1.050 0.11 1193 -9.554 <.0001

is the most interesting result

interesting egg results

if using combined egg data:

1:8H - 1:8S -42.8 6.88 75 -6.217 <.0001 1:2S - 1:8S -79.2 6.88 75 -11.511 <.0001

much prefer to lay their eggs on a soft diet

summary of what has been found

experiment 1a and 1b = 1:8 and 1:2

feeding

experiment 1a day is significant but combined day analysis shows there isn’t much preference but 1:2H is least preferred to all else

experiment 1b day is significant but combined day analysis shows they like 1:2S the most and all else is equiv, 1:2H also least preferred

oviposition experiment 1a they prefer to lay their eggs on soft 1:8, then hard 1:8 rather than 1:2 soft or hard

experiment 1b they prefer to lay their eggs on soft 1:8, then hard 1:8 rather than 1:2 soft or hard

experiment 2 = 8:1 and 1:2

feeding day can only just not be used, but they go to 8:1S and 8:1H before they go to 1:2S and 1:2H

oviposition they lay their eggs on soft 1:2S then soft 8:1S before they lay their eggs on 1:2H and 8:1H - do not really like this diet at all

experiment 3 = 8:1 and 1:8

feeding day is significant but combined data analysis shows they like the soft 1:8 and 8:1 equally, then feed on 8:1H a bit after, but 1:8H is much less preferred

oviposition they really like to lay their eggs on 1:8 soft (which was expected), then 8:1 soft, 1:8 hard soon after, but 8:1 hard is not really liked at all

two factor test!!
